place.name: COVERACK
place.gazetteerText: COVERACK, a village on the SE coast of Cornwall; in a cove of its own name, 2 miles N by E of Black Head, and 10½ S of Falmouth. It is highly picturesque; and the rocks around it show veins of hornblende in masses of serpentine. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
